				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				DO NOT NERF MULTIQUESTING!<BR>
<BR>
What right does anyone have to tell me how I can and can't make money? It's OK to sell a FBSS, but not Jboots? If your that concerned with the whole idea of quests and multiquesting, just get rid of ALL no-drop items. Do you actually believe some things should NOT be for sale? If thet is true, why have ANYTHING for sale? What is the point of a limited economy? Has anyone even considered the fact that it really boils down to preference? I like camping the AC, but I do not like lower Guk.<BR>
<BR>
&quot;Hey man, I'll trade you Jboots for a FBSS.&quot;<BR>
&quot;Opps, sorry, can't do that anymore.&quot;<BR>
<BR>
I have met so many good friends doing the whole multiquesting thing that if they take it out, (which to me sounds like it's already a done deal),it will simply discourage contact with other players.<BR>
 <BR>
&quot;No, I won't group with you, I need to get my own quest items and you are not allowed to help me anymore, sorry.&quot;<BR>
<BR>
What about the people who already made the cash, but don't want to spend the time doing a quest? Is there really any legitimate reason they should NOT be allowed to buy certain things? I don't think so. I could care less if someone is able to buy an epic item. Why shouldn't they? If they saved the plat for it, let them spend it! Great, now I have over a million plat, and can't spend it on anything I want or need.<BR>
<BR>
Bottom line is this: You (Verant) have a bunch of frustrated whiners out there who don't have as much time as they want to get the game items they desire, so they point the fingers at all the people who actually have the time to get those same items. The people with no time just simply don't want to have to pay for that difference. They want the item handed to them without any plat or time invested to aquire it.<BR>
<BR>
If this is a player based economy, then make it an ECONOMY!! ALL items are for sale and have a price. Or none at all. Either it's an open market, or its communist distribution of wealth.<BR>
I spent the time camping the item, I spent the time killing the mob, I should have the right to sell it for the price I set, to whom I want.<BR>
<BR>
As far as the turning in the wrong items? Tough excriment!! You shoulda listened closer to the clues, or read up on the quest before hand.<BR>
<BR>
Verant: You spewed your lame-ass &quot;Risk vs. Rewards&quot; to us on endless occassions, now you want to take the whole risk out of making a mistake that the player alone is responsible for out of the equasion. Now I won't even worry if I'm right or not with my components, because if I get them wrong, hey, who cares? It won't come out of my pocket anymore!<BR>
<BR>
The double standard that Verant uses sickens me to death.  <BR>
<BR>
(Come on,  Horizons!)<BR>
<BR>

