				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I see people whining about being ks'd while attempting to get the ac well welcome to reality he is a target of opportunity and some people will always ks him even if they can not multiquest j boots.  I have hunted him for a week straight with my guild and we got 5 rings and had 2 ks's and 2 instances where we missed drawing first blood.  I happened to be running to Fp one day triggered the spawn and he popped first time and I was the highest level in the zone and no one was camping him (I couldn't believe it either).  Guess what I got 9k for multiquesting for j boots.  I feel multiquesting is a necessary part of the game and should be left alone.  Individuals should be sure of the order they are turning things in and that they are giving it to the right npc.  Eliminating multiquesting will not eliminate ksing and will not eliminate farming (ac ring has nice ac and int stats). As<BR>
for the level 31 paladin I saw earlier trying for j boots good luck I killed him at lvl 36 solo and I had Fm and had to use loh and he almost got me to a bubble.<BR>
