			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Before I make my thoughts clear to everyone.  Verant needs to ask themselves a few questions:<BR>
<BR>
1) Was Multi-questing an intentional effect or is it an undocumented feature (microsofts term for BUG).<BR>
<BR>
2) If you return items turned in incorrectly for a quest how will that effect other quests in the game (corrupt guards???)<BR>
<BR>
3) One of the things that makes Everquest so vibrant is the in-game economy, how will these changes effect the in-game economy?  Will those changes make the economy better or worse?<BR>
<BR>
1) With these questions in mind.  When I first heard about Multi-questing I thought it was broken.  Why should I be able to get J. Boots by having someone else turn in the AC ring and me the rest of the items?  It might be a good idea for a future quest for a group of people to have to turn in specific items in a specific order but that is not part of todays discussion.  I feel that Multi-questing CAUSES people to KS &amp; play in a generally unacceptable manner.<BR>
<BR>
2) Returning Quest items that are wrong sounds on the surface as a GREAT idea.  I would vote for this, but I would also suggest Verant take a close look at all of the quests and determine what quests might get modified to take care of any problems that this might provide.<BR>

				</font>
