&#8220;All Verant seems to do is institute changes that piss off their most loyal customers, namely those with high end critters.&#8221;<BR>
<BR>
Yes, okay, but I also pay a monthly subscription to play the game and complete quests and as far as I am aware my subscription does not increase with level!<BR>
<BR>
&#8220;To all you people gloating over &quot;nerfing the ubers&quot;.....god, what low expectations you must have.&#8221;<BR>
<BR>
This isn&#8217;t &#8220;nerfing the ubers&#8221;. It is an attempt to stop greedy ubers taking advantage of an apparent loophole in the no-drop rules.<BR>
<BR>
&#8220;you take joy in hurting those that have achieved more.&#8221;<BR>
<BR>
I respect your achievements, I just don&#8217;t respect your right to prevent others from achieving by monopolising spawns.<BR>
<BR>
&#8220;Lastly, this is the most messed up business model I've ever seen.&#8221;<BR>
<BR>
Depends on how you look at it. If VI have to admit that in order to play the game you have to have played it from day one because otherwise people will not let you into their exclusive club, how many new customers would VI attract?<BR>
<BR>
&#8220;They have already written the code for this, it's a done deal, multi-questing is dead.&#8221;<BR>
<BR>
Just in case you thought I would disagree with everything you said, I agree wholeheartedly with this one &#8211; they probably have already decided. This is implied by the limited input from the originator of the thread.<BR>
<BR>
Sorry, but we are in their world now!<BR>
